main event: On December 6, 1959, military ground radar observed several triple objects traveling from northwest to southeast, disappearing or flaming out after two minutes of observation. A satellite was launched from Cape Canaveral around the same time, which was considered as a possible object viewed.
interesting points: The objects were observed using military ground radar, adding credibility to the sighting.
The sighting coincided with the launch of a satellite from Cape Canaveral, potentially providing an alternative explanation.
The objects traveled at very high altitude, further adding to the mystery of their nature.
The report indicates that the classification was cancelled, and the evaluation remained inconclusive, leaving the nature of the objects unknown.
The document involved multiple military sources, including the Navy Department and the Air Force, suggesting a high level of official interest.
sighted object: Several triple objects traveling from northwest to southeast
location: 95 miles southeast of Pt. Tuna, Bahamas
